  <h3 class="w3-center">ABOUT ME</h3>
  <p class="w3-center"><em>Psychology Major and Visual Arts Minor</em></p>
  <p>Hello! I'm Shumita Littlefield, a 21 year old junior at Boston University. I grew up in Newton, Massachusetts, a suburb outside of Boston. I love creating art, whether it be sketching, painting, sculpting, or sewing.</p>
 <p> I am a Psychology Major, focusing on developmental and children's psychology. I am also a Visual Arts Minor, with a focus in illustration and graphic design. Currently, I am an Undergrad Research Assistant for the Developming Minds project at the Boston University Child Cognition Lab, as well as the illustrator for a start-up company formed by a fellow BU Student.</p>
 <p>I have skills in drawing/illustrating, sewing, sculpting, and graphic design. I have experience in Procreate, Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, InDesign, and Premiere Pro. Some of my other skills include working with children, customer service, organization skills, time management, teamwork, and attention to detail.</p>
  <div class="w3-row">
    <div class="w3-col m6 w3-center w3-padding-large">
      <p><b><i class="fa fa-user w3-margin-right"></i>Shumita Littlefield</b></p><br>
      <img src="photo_of_me.jpg" class="w3-round w3-image w3-opacity w3-hover-opacity-off" alt="Photo of Me" width="500" height="333">
    </div>

    <!-- Hide this text on small devices -->
    <div class="w3-col m6 w3-hide-small w3-padding-large">
      <p>In my current work, I illustrate pictures of animals to aid children in imagining the effects of evolution.</p>
      <p>I also illustrate for Idori, a company founded by a student at the Questrom School of Business. The company's goal is to teach children about sustainability, and create an impact that promotes more earth-friendly living. Idori aims to do this through stuffed animals and picture books containing stories about various environmental dangers. So far three picture books have been planned, and the first book is reaching its release date.
    </div>
